1) Provide a number for how your onboarding to Vega and NP (as a whole) has gone thus far. You can give two numbers if you want for Vega and NP separately.

For both NP and Vega, I would score the onboarding process a 4/10. The reasons for that score are as follows:

1. At the beginning of the onboarding process, there wasn’t much clarity. It was difficult to understand the scope of everything we were doing, and it wasn’t always clear who I should reach out to with questions because I didn’t have a good understanding of who was responsible for what on the team.
2. As with most onboarding experiences, I understand that there is a lot of information to absorb in a short amount of time. However, I found that being directed to read through the Confluence board to understand what Vega is wasn’t especially helpful. The board is extensive, and it was difficult to determine where to start or what information was most important.
3. It was also difficult to set up my workspace environment because most of the team used Ubuntu while I was using RHEL, and the RHEL environment had not yet been fully configured.
4. The first few meetings were challenging to follow. Everyone seemed to have different perspectives on the tasks at hand, and discussions often moved quickly between topics. I understand and appreciate the free-flowing nature of those conversations, but as someone new to the team and trying to absorb a large amount of information, it was sometimes difficult to identify the key points and understand what I should focus on.

