2) What has been the most helpful resource you’ve had while joining the team?

The most helpful resource has been the one-on-one meetings with team members. Those conversations helped me better understand the team’s processes, the work being done, and the context behind many of the discussions. They also made the larger team meetings much easier to follow and understand.

⸻

3) What has been the least helpful resource you’ve had while joining the team?

The least helpful resources were the Confluence pages that lacked a clear objective or explanation of what I was expected to learn from them. Similarly, simply cloning GitLab repositories and exploring the codebase without a specific goal was not particularly effective for me.

I tend to learn best when I’m given a concrete task or objective that requires me to work within a repository. It is much easier for me to understand how a system works when I can learn by doing rather than trying to absorb information in the abstract.

