7) Please list any ideas or resources that you think should be included in a “Day 1 Joining Vega UI” package.

One thing I would have found valuable early on is a clear, high-level overview of what Vega/NP is trying to build and how the different pieces fit together. A “bird’s-eye view” of the system, its goals, and the team’s responsibilities would provide useful context before diving into the technical details.

From there, it could be supplemented with additional meetings or documentation that explore specific areas in greater depth.

I also think it would be helpful if early onboarding meetings were more structured. During my first meetings, it was sometimes difficult to follow the discussion because while one team lead was explaining a concept or system, someone else would interject with a related topic or a different perspective. While those conversations are valuable and often necessary, they can make it harder for a new team member to understand the main points and retain the information being presented.

